HEADWORD: Centurion
<hw>Cen*tu"ri*on</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>centurio</ets>, fr. <ets>centuria</ets>; cf. F.
<ets>centurion</ets>. See <er>Century</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Rom.
Hist.)</fld> <def>A military officer who commanded a minor division of
the Roman army; a captain of a century.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>centurion</qex> of the hand called the Italian band.</q>
<rj><qau>Acts x. 1.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Century</ent>⟦br⟧
